## 46:23. Order of elimination: Mephisto (via Stuka), Felino (Mistico), Star Jr. (Caristico), Stuka Jr. (Negro Casas), Soberano (Atlantis), Negro Casas (Dragon Rojo), Felino Jr. (Mistico), Atlantis JJr. (Angel de Oro), Mistico was DQ (accidentally removed Dragon Rojo's mask), Dragon Rojo (Caristico), Caristico (Angel de Oro) leaving Angel de Oro the winner. Dragon Rojo's first match in two years, replacing Niebla Roja (scheduled in December.) Felino Jr. (ex-Tiger) debut under that name, which had been given to him in November.
3) Cuatrero, Forastero, Sansón b Euforia, Gran Guerrero, Último Guerrero  (c) [CMLL TRIOS]

4) Volador Jr.  (c) b El Bandido [NWA WELTER]
## 28:43, Volador took falls 2/3 for his seventh defense. Originally scheduled for 09-25, postponed due to Bandido COVID-19 infection, postponed in November and December.

3) Faby Apache b Lady Shani, Flammer, Chik Tormenta, Lady Maravilla, Sexy Star [Reina De Reinas]
## Vacant title (Taya went to WWE.) The mystery wrestler was Sexy Star (Hija de Gatuebla, not the original.) Eliminations went Flammer (Chik Tormenta), Maravilla (Sexy Star), Sexy Star (Shani), Shani (Tormenta) and Tormenta (Faby Apache.) Deonna Purrazzo, on commentary for the match, issued a challenge for an Impact Knockouts championship versus AAA Reina de Reinas championship match. Faby Apache eventually agreed, though was still attacked by Purrazzo.
4) Laredo Kid b Texano Jr., Murder Clown, Aerostar, Drago, Abismo Negro Jr., Hijo Del Vikingo, Myzteziz Jr. [Rey de Reyes]
## Elimination order: Myzteziz, Aerostar, Drago, Vikingo, Abismo Negro, Murder and Laredo Kid beat Texano to win.
5) Pagano, Psycho Clown NF Chessman, Sam Adonis
## Sam Adonis was the surpise wrestler. A vehicle with two mystery wrestlers came to the ring, attacking the tecnicos. They revealed themsevles as Puma King and Diamante Azul (exiting CMLL), then also attacked Chessman. Adonis, King and Azul are La Empresa, and showed a video of Andrade challenging Kenny Omega for TripleMania and Psycho Clown for some other date.

## Originally a EDM TRIOS semifinal, but the tournament has been abandoned after Pasion Kristal's death. Los Sencillos were originally replaced by Guadalajara, Monterrey, and Sinaloa, but instead of a team of Juniors faced them. First appearance for Guerrero Maya Jr. (long ago Multifacetico) on an IWRG show since 2009. Los Traumas returned to tease a partnership with Infernal & Fresero, an angle they had done an indie show the day prior. A clip of the Trauma appearance was posted by Mas Lucha and later removed; perhaps it was an unauthorized angle. Traumas, Demonio and Fresero would indeed form a group and make anti-IWRG statements following this show.

** Verano de Escandalo, 2021
1) Arez, Chik Tormenta b Abismo Negro Jr., Flammer and Mamba, Mr. Iguana [#1 Contenders, AAA MIXED TAG]
## Mamba replaced Maximo. Villano 3 Jr. and Maravilla stared down the winners post match
2) Hijo Del Vikingo b Kamikaze, Komander, Aramis, Látigo, Toxin [Alas de Oro]
## No names announced ahead of time. Kamikaze is the debuting Ninja Mack under a different gimmick (but they talked about his background in a specific way to make it obvious and put him over strong in commentary.) Vikingo got the win and a trophy
3) Deonna Purrazzo b Lady Shani
## Purrazzo would not release her armbar on Shani until Faby Apace made the save.
4) Carta Brava Jr., Mocho Cota Jr., Tito Santana b Faby Apache, Laredo Kid, Niño Hamburguesa
## Hamburguesa took the pin
5) Rey Escorpión, Taurus, Texano Jr.  (c) b Monsther Clown, Murder Clown, Psycho Clown [AAA TRIOS]
## brawl started before the match. Escorpion again beat Psycho, putting him through a makeshift table with thumbtacks using the Guerrero Special.
6) Flammer, La Hiedra, Maravilla b Big Mami, Pimpinela Escarlata, Sexy Star
## Las Toxicas won with help from Mamba
7) Toxin, Villano III Jr. b Komander, Octagón Jr.
## Villano III fouled Octagon Jr. to beat him
8) Chessman, Parka Negra, Súper Fly b Aerostar, Drago, Pagano
## Super Fly fouled Aerostar to pin him, then Empresa beat up both teams

AAA TV (SAT) 08/14/2021 Arena Ciudad de Mexico, Azcapotzalco, Distrito Federal [AAA, https://criteriohidalgo.com/la-copa/gana-psycho-pese-a-traicion-de-su-hermana Criterio Hidalgo, https://www.esto.com.mx/555121-kenny-omega-retuvo-el-megacampeonato-aaa-en-triplemania-29/ ESTO, Lucha Central, https://www.maslucha.com/resultados-triplemania-29-de-lucha-libre-triple-a/ Mas Lucha, https://www.rderudo.com.mx/ric-flair-refuerzo-de-lujo-para-andrade-el-idolo/ R de Rudo, https://www.voicesofwrestling.com/2021/08/15/aaa-triplemania-xxix-august-14-results-review/ Voices of Wrestling]
** TripleMania XXIX
1) Aracno, Estrella Cosmica, Leyenda Americana b Picadura Letal, Terror Purpura, Venenoide
## 12:42. A Marvel Lucha Libre match. El Furioso (Hulk, Murder Clown) made the save. El Engañoso (Loki) taunted the heroes from the video screen.
2) Mr. Iguana b Myzteziz Jr., Carta Brava, Aramis, Tito Santana, Niño Hamburguesa, Drago, Pimpinela Escarlata, Argenis, Mamba, Mocho Cota Jr., Villano III Jr. [Copa Bardahl]
## 18:26. Parka Negra, Super Fly, Octagon Jr. all got involved. Mr. Iguana won the Copa. NGD appeared after, attacking Mr. Iguana and then taking out Aramis & Octagon Jr. as they tried to make the save. Poder del Norte faced off with NGD until they were attacked by La Empresa, who gave NGD t-shirts to join their group.
3) Deonna Purrazzo  (c) b Faby Apache  (c) [Reina De Reinas, IMPACT KNOCKOUT]
## 9:46. Maravilla and Tirantes helped Purrazzo beat Faby with an armbar. Purrazzo is a doubel champion.
4) Fénix, Pentagón Jr. b Hijo Del Vikingo, Laredo Kid and Brian Cage, Taurus [AAA TAG]
## 14:28. Fenix & Penta beat Vikingo with a two man Fear Factor on Vikingo. Mystery person was Cage.
5) DMT Azul, Puma King, Sam Adonis b Chessman, Murder Clown, Pagano
## 8:43. Chessman and Pagano fought, costing their team  the match.
6) Kenny Omega  (c) b Andrade [AAA MEGA]
## 24:41. Konnan accompanied Omega, Ric Flair appeared with Andrade and helped Andrade during the match. Omega still won using the belt.
7) Psycho Clown b Rey Escorpión [mask, hair]
## 23:53. Goya Kong turned on Rey Escorpion for no reason (except AAA always does that) but Psycho won seconds later with a tapatia. Escorpion got his hair cut in the ring and both expressed respect for each other.

## 10:49. One fall. Cavernario won cleanly with La Nieblina. Felino got his head shaved in the ring. Cavernario stated in post match that his own challenge left was a hair match with Ultimo Guerrero (as he had named in pre-match interviews.)

## 10:19. Hijo del Tirantes fast counted a pin after Tirantes Sr. had tried to help Faby Apache. A vignette with Taya teasing her return and a title challenge at Deonna Purrazzo aired.
3) Cuatrero, Forastero, Sansón b Carta Brava Jr., Mocho Cota Jr., Tito Santana and Abismo Negro Jr., Arez, Psicosis II [AAA TRIOS, #1 Contenders]
## 13:25. Cuatrero & Forastero beat Arez. Ciberentico returned to AAA prior to the match, promising to destroy Konnan and lead the Vipers. He ran in after the match, laying out the six non-Vipers.
4) Diamante Azul (Indie), Puma King, Sam Adonis b Chessman, Dave The Clown, Murder Clown
## 14:08. Empresa pinned Dave the Clown after other identified clowns revealed themselves to be La Empresa members. Chessman was stretchered out, though not until Adonis missed a moonsault on him.
5) Dragón Lee (Indie), Dralistico b Laredo Kid, Willie Mack
## 13:54. Dragon Lee beat surprise wrestler Willie Mack, who became quickly popular. Hermanos Lee repeated their challenge for the whomever end up tag team champions. Dragon Lee also challenged Laredo Kid for his Cruiserweight title, which Laredo Kid accepted.
6) Cash Wheeler, Dax Harwood  (c) b Fénix, Pentagón Jr. [AAA TAG, Ladder]
## FTR and Lucha Brothers yelled at each other and brawled prior to the fifth match. This was made a ladder match for no established reason and with no explanation. Vickie Guerrero, seconding FTR, threw powder in Penta's face to cause him to fall backwards through a table, allowing Cash to get the belts.
7) Cain Velasquez, Pagano, Psycho Clown b LA Park, Rey Escorpión, Taurus
## Cain Velasquez wore a mask in the style of the Arizona State Sun Devils. The crowd was strongly pro-Park and anti-Cain as a result. Cain had Park in a submission until Park's son ran in. Park had the advantage but was distracted by a Rayo de Jalisco Jr. appearance (and Rayo mistakenly starting his promo.) Velasquez submitted Park. Park and the rudos walked by Rayo without incident as he came to the ring to talk about his family's history in Monterrey and his own in AAA. NGD appeared to confront Rayo and were eventually run off by the tecnicos to boos.
8) Hijo Del Vikingo b Samuray del Sol, Bandido, Bobby Fish, Jay Lethal [AAA MEGA]
## 14:22. scheduled as Omega 7th defense. AAA stripped the title from Omega on November 22nd because Omega would be unable to compete due to injury, then started naming challengers over the following days. All wrestlers generally worked as tecnicos. First pinfall to a win, with Vikingo defeating Sol via Cuerno del Vikingo reverse 450 splash. No one else felt as close to winning. The AAA tecnicos celebrated with Vikingo. Vikingo said he wanted to defend against Omega.
